President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Judge Christina Reiss to the United States District Court for the District of Vermont. Judge Reiss currently serves as a State Judge in the Lamoille District of the Vermont Superior Court and Vermont District Courts. She has an impressive judicial career and is known for her formidable intellect and integrity. Judge Reiss received her Bachelor's degree from St. Michael's College in Vermont and her law degree from the University of Arizona College of Law in 1989. Before her appointment to the bench in 2004, she worked as a litigator specializing in various areas of law. She has received a unanimous well-qualified rating from the ABA and is being nominated for the District Court bench in Vermont.